  "texts": [
    "Assume for a contradiction that (M, g) is locally homogeneous.",
    "Then, (B 2, g B) is locally homogeneous by Lemma 4.11, and hence has constant Gauss curvature since dim B = 2.",
    "By (20b), h * g B = Ric g B + 1 2 g is a constant multiple of g B.",
    "In particular, h * g sym, and hence also h * g C sym = tr ΦΦ *, either vanishes identically or vanishes nowhere.",
    "The claim now follows since tr ΦΦ * vanishes at b ∈ B if and only if γ b = 0, and γ has exactly 2g -2 -2d zeroes (counted with multiplicity) since it is a holomorphic section of a line bundle of degree 2g -2 -2d."
  ],
